{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861539637,"sessionID":"ses_286678f41ffeN9616wg6MWphlY","part":{"id":"prt_d7998935b001qwFmkrGSbpvows","messageID":"msg_d79988854001NpsYDE5mP0vTLy","sessionID":"ses_286678f41ffeN9616wg6MWphlY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_39f50295c68b4bbe953e0927","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP daemon in the `pkg/picod` module. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Secure API Access** - Protect PicoD HTTP endpoints with RSA-based JWT authentication\n8: 2. **Token Validation** - Validate JWT tokens signed with RSA private keys using the corresponding public key\n9: 3. **Request Authorization** - Intercept and authenticate incoming HTTP requests before allowing access to command execution APIs\n10: 4. **Flexible Configuration** - Support configuration via environment variables and command-line flags\n11: 5. **Health Endpoint Protection** - Optionally protect the health check endpoint with JWT authentication\n12: \n13: This implementation builds upon the PicoD execution infrastructure established in AR-015 and provides the security layer required for multi-tenant code interpreter deployments.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** S\n20: \n21: This AR covers:\n22: \n23: - **In scope:**\n24:   - JWT middleware implementation (`middleware.go`)\n25:   - JWT token validation logic (`jwt.go`)\n26:   - RSA key handling utilities (`crypto.go`)\n27:   - Configuration via environment variables and flags\n28:   - Unit tests with mocked tokens and keys\n29:   - Integration tests with real HTTP server\n30:   - Error handling and logging\n31: \n32: - **Out of scope:**\n33:   - JWT token generation (handled by external auth service)\n34:   - Token refresh mechanisms\n35:   - User/role-based authorization (only authentication)\n36:   - OAuth2 or other authentication protocols\n37:   - Session management (covered in AR-013)\n38:   - PicoD HTTP server implementation (covered in `code-execution/` specs)\n39: \n40: ## Current State Analysis\n41: \n42: ### Existing PicoD Infrastructure\n43: \n44: The current PicoD system has command execution infrastructure:\n45: \n46: 1. **PicoD Core** (`pkg/picod/picod.go`):\n47:    - Main `PicoD` struct with sandbox ID, work directory, limits, and security options\n48:    - Functional options pattern for configuration\n49:    - Structured logging with klog\n50: \n51: 2. **Command Execution** (`pkg/picod/executor.go`):\n52:    - `Run()` and `Start()` methods for command execution\n53:    - Resource limit enforcement (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n54:    - Output capture and streaming\n55: \n56: 3. **Security Module** (`pkg/picod/security.go`):\n57:    - Command validation and path safety checks\n58:    - Privilege dropping and capability management\n59:    - Allowlist-based command selection\n60: \n61: 4. **Configuration** (`pkg/picod/config.go`):\n62:    - Environment variable loading\n63:    - Default values for resource limits\n64: \n65: ### Gaps Identified\n66: \n67: 1. **No HTTP authentication** - PicoD HTTP daemon has no authentication layer\n68: 2. **No JWT validation** - Cannot validate JWT tokens from incoming requests\n69: 3. **No RSA key handling** - Missing utilities for loading and using RSA public keys\n70: 4. **No middleware pattern** - No HTTP middleware for request interception\n71: 5. **Health endpoint exposed** - Health check endpoint is publicly accessible\n72: \n73: ### PicoD HTTP Context\n74: \n75: Per `code-execution/design.md` and `code-execution/spec.md`:\n76: - PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail\n77: - Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n78: - CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default: current working directory)\n79: - Server uses `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n80: - Authentication modes: `picod` (JWT required) or `none` (no auth)\n81: \n82: ### Kubernetes Client-Go Context\n83: \n84: Per `deployment/client-go.md`:\n85: - Generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n86: - `CodeInterpreter` CRD supports `AuthMode` enum (`picod` or `none`)\n87: - Workload manager injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode=picod`\n88: - Public key provided as base64-encoded PEM string\n89: \n90: ## Proposed Changes\n91: \n92: ### 1. JWT Middleware (`middleware.go`)\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: // JWTMiddleware is HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens\n96: type JWTMiddleware struct {\n97:     // publicKey is the RSA public key for token validation\n98:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n99:     \n100:     // skipPaths is a list of paths to skip authentication\n101:     skipPaths map[string]bool\n102:     \n103:     // logger is the structured logger\n104:     logger klog.Logger\n105: }\n106: \n107: // NewJWTMiddleware creates a new JWT middleware\n108: func NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, skipPaths ...string) *JWTMiddleware\n109: \n110: // Middleware returns the HTTP middleware handler\n111: func (m *JWTMiddleware) Middleware(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n112: \n113: // extractToken extracts the JWT token from the Authorization header\n114: func (m *JWTMiddleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n115: \n116: // shouldSkip checks if a path should skip authentication\n117: func (m *JWTMiddleware) shouldSkip(path string) bool\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ### 2. JWT Validation (`jwt.go`)\n121: \n122: ```go\n123: // Claims represents JWT token claims\n124: type Claims struct {\n125:     // Subject is the token subject\n126:     Sub string `json:\"sub\"`\n127:     \n128:     // Issuer is the token issuer\n129:     Iss string `json:\"iss\"`\n130:     \n131:     // Audience is the token audience\n132:     Aud string `json:\"aud\"`\n133:     \n134:     // Expiration time\n135:     Exp int64 `json:\"exp\"`\n136:     \n137:     // Issued at\n138:     Iat int64 `json:\"iat\"`\n139:     \n140:     // Custom claims for AgentCube\n141:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandbox_id,omitempty\"`\n142:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n143: }\n144: \n145: // Validate validates the JWT claims\n146: func (c *Claims) Validate(now time.Time) error\n147: \n148: // ParseAndValidate parses and validates a JWT token\n149: func ParseAndValidate(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) (*Claims, error)\n150: \n151: // VerifySignature verifies the JWT signature\n152: func VerifySignature(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) error\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### 3. RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n156: \n157: ```go\n158: // LoadPublicKey loads an RSA public key from PEM-encoded data\n159: func LoadPublicKey(pemData []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n160: \n161: // LoadPublicKeyFromBase64 loads an RSA public key from base64-encoded PEM\n162: func LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(base64PEM string) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n163: \n164: // ParsePEM parses PEM-encoded data and returns the RSA public key\n165: func ParsePEM(pemBlock *pem.Block) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)\n166: \n167: // GenerateKeyPair generates an RSA key pair for testing\n168: func GenerateKeyPair(bits int) (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)\n169: ```\n170: \n171: ### 4. Configuration\n172: \n173: #### Environment Variables\n174: \n175: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n176: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n177: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | Conditional | `` | Base64-encoded PEM RSA public key (required if `-auth=picod`) |\n178: | `PICOD_AUTH_MODE` | No | `none` | Authentication mode (`picod` or `none`) |\n179: | `PICOD_AUTH_SKIP_PATHS` | No | `/health` | Comma-separated list of paths to skip auth |\n180: \n181: #### Command-Line Flags\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: // Add to existing PicoD flag parsing\n185: flag.StringVar(&authMode, \"auth\", \"none\", \"Authentication mode: picod or none\")\n186: flag.StringVar(&publicKeyPEM, \"public-key\", \"\", \"RSA public key (base64-encoded PEM)\")\n187: flag.StringVar(&skipPaths, \"skip-paths\", \"/health\", \"Comma-separated paths to skip auth\")\n188: ```\n189: \n190: ### 5. Error Handling\n191: \n192: ```go\n193: // AuthError represents an authentication error\n194: type AuthError struct {\n195:     // Type is the error type\n196:     Type AuthErrorType\n197:     \n198:     // Message is the error message\n199:     Message string\n200:     \n201:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n202:     Underlying error\n203: }\n204: \n205: type AuthErrorType string\n206: \n207: const (\n208:     AuthErrorMissingToken  AuthErrorType = \"missing_token\"\n209:     AuthErrorInvalidToken  AuthErrorType = \"invalid_token\"\n210:     AuthErrorExpiredToken  AuthErrorType = \"expired_token\"\n211:     AuthErrorInvalidSig    AuthErrorType = \"invalid_signature\"\n212:     AuthErrorInvalidClaims AuthErrorType = \"invalid_claims\"\n213:     AuthErrorInternal      AuthErrorType = \"internal_error\"\n214: )\n215: \n216: // HTTPResponse returns the appropriate HTTP status code\n217: func (e *AuthError) HTTPStatus() int\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### 6. HTTP Response Helpers\n221: \n222: ```go\n223: // WriteJSON writes a JSON response\n224: func WriteJSON(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})\n225: \n226: // WriteError writes an error response\n227: func WriteError(w http.ResponseWriter, err error)\n228: \n229: // HealthResponse represents a health check response\n230: type HealthResponse struct {\n231:     // Status is the health status\n232:     Status string `json:\"status\"`\n233:     \n234:     // Timestamp is the current time\n235:     Timestamp time.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n236:     \n237:     // SandboxID is the sandbox identifier\n238:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandbox_id,omitempty\"`\n239: }\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ### 7. Integration with Existing Code\n243: \n244: ```go\n245: // SetupHTTPServer creates the HTTP server with JWT middleware\n246: func SetupHTTPServer(picod *PicoD, config *Config) (*http.Server, error) {\n247:     mux := http.NewServeMux()\n248:     \n249:     // Health endpoint (optionally protected)\n250:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/health\", handleHealth(picod))\n251:     \n252:     // Command execution endpoints (protected)\n253:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/api/v1/execute\", handleExecute(picod))\n254:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/api/v1/execute/stream\", handleExecuteStream(picod))\n255:     \n256:     // Apply JWT middleware\n257:     var handler http.Handler = mux\n258:     if config.AuthMode == \"picod\" {\n259:         publicKey, err := LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(config.PublicKeyPEM)\n260:         if err != nil {\n261:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load public key: %w\", err)\n262:         }\n263:         \n264:         middleware := NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey, config.SkipPaths...)\n265:         handler = middleware.Middleware(mux)\n266:     }\n267:     \n268:     return &http.Server{\n269:         Addr:              fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", config.Port),\n270:         Handler:           handler,\n271:         ReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n272:     }, nil\n273: }\n274: ```\n275: \n276: ## Impact Analysis\n277: \n278: ### Dependencies\n279: \n280: | Package | Purpose |\n281: |---------|---------|\n282: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA signature verification |\n283: | `crypto/x509` | X.509 key parsing |\n284: | `encoding/pem` | PEM decoding |\n285: | `encoding/base64` | Base64 decoding |\n286: | `encoding/json` | JSON encoding/decoding |\n287: | `net/http` | HTTP middleware |\n288: | `strings` | String manipulation |\n289: | `time` | Time-based token validation |\n290: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n291: \n292: ### Affected Components\n293: \n294: 1. **PicoD HTTP Server** (`code-execution/`): Will integrate JWT middleware into HTTP server setup\n295: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will configure auth mode and inject public key\n296: 3. **Code Interpreter Controller** (`pkg/controller/`): Will set `AuthMode` on `CodeInterpreter` spec\n297: 4. **Authentication Service** (external): Will generate JWT tokens for clients\n298: 5. **Client Applications**: Will include JWT tokens in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n299: \n300: ### Backward Compatibility\n301: \n302: - Default auth mode is `none` (no authentication) for backward compatibility\n303: - Existing deployments without `AuthMode=picod` continue to work unchanged\n304: - Public key injection is optional and only required when `AuthMode=picod`\n305: - Health endpoint can be configured to skip authentication\n306: \n307: ### Risk Assessment\n308: \n309: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n310: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n311: | Token forgery | Low | Critical | Use RSA-256/512 signatures, verify with strong crypto |\n312: | Key leakage | Low | Critical | Keys managed by Kubernetes secrets, not in code |\n313: | Token replay | Medium | High | Include `iat` and `exp` claims, use short-lived tokens |\n314: | Clock skew | Medium | Medium | Allow configurable clock skew tolerance (30s) |\n315: | Performance overhead | Low | Low | RSA verification is fast (<1ms per request) |\n316: | DoS via invalid tokens | Medium | Low | Rate limiting, early rejection of malformed tokens |\n317: \n318: ## Alternatives Considered\n319: \n320: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing JWT Library (e.g., golang-jwt/jwt)\n321: \n322: **Approach**: Leverage the popular `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` library\n323: \n324: **Pros**:\n325: - Battle-tested, widely used\n326: - Handles edge cases (clock skew, token parsing)\n327: - Active community support\n328: - Supports multiple signature algorithms\n329: \n330: **Cons**:\n331: - Additional dependency\n332: - May be overkill for simple RSA verification\n333: - Larger binary size\n334: \n335: **Decision**: Use a minimal custom implementation for simplicity and control, but structure code to easily swap in `golang-jwt/jwt` if needed. The custom implementation will follow JWT standards (RFC 7519) for compatibility.\n336: \n337: ### Alternative 2: Kubernetes ServiceAccount Token\n338: \n339: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes native ServiceAccount tokens for authentication\n340: \n341: **Pros**:\n342: - Native Kubernetes integration\n343: - No additional key management\n344: - Automatic token rotation\n345: \n346: **Cons**:\n347: - Requires Kubernetes API access for validation\n348: - Tightly couples PicoD to Kubernetes\n349: - More complex validation logic\n350: - Not suitable for non-Kubernetes deployments\n351: \n352: **Decision**: Use RSA-based JWT for deployment flexibility and simpler validation. PicoD should work both inside and outside Kubernetes.\n353: \n354: ### Alternative 3: mTLS (Mutual TLS)\n355: \n356: **Approach**: Use mutual TLS for client authentication\n357: \n358: **Pros**:\n359: - Strong security (certificate-based)\n360: - Built into Go's `http.Server`\n361: - No custom token handling\n362: \n363: **Cons**:\n364: - Complex certificate management\n365: - Requires CA infrastructure\n366: - Harder to debug\n367: - Less flexible for distributed systems\n368: \n369: **Decision**: Use JWT for simpler token-based authentication. mTLS is better suited for service-to-service communication at the infrastructure level.\n370: \n371: ### Alternative 4: API Key Authentication\n372: \n373: **Approach**: Use simple API keys in headers\n374: \n375: **Pros**:\n376: - Simple implementation\n377: - Easy to debug\n378: - Low overhead\n379: \n380: **Cons**:\n381: - No standard claims structure\n382: - Harder to distribute and rotate\n383: - No built-in expiration\n384: - Less secure (symmetric keys)\n385: \n386: **Decision**: Use JWT with RSA signatures for better security, standard claims, and asymmetric key distribution.\n387: \n388: ## Testing Strategy\n389: \n390: ### Unit Tests\n391: \n392: 1. **TestJWTMiddleware_ValidToken**: Valid JWT token passes through\n393: 2. **TestJWTMiddleware_MissingToken**: Missing token returns 401\n394: 3. **TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidToken**: Malformed token returns 401\n395: 4. **TestJWTMiddleware_ExpiredToken**: Expired token returns 401\n396: 5. **TestJWTMiddleware_SkipPath**: Health endpoint skips auth\n397: 6. **TestParseAndValidate_Success**: Valid token parses claims correctly\n398: 7. **TestParseAndValidate_InvalidSignature**: Tampered token fails verification\n399: 8. **TestClaims_Validate_Expired**: Expired claims fail validation\n400: 9. **TestClaims_Validate_Future**: Not-yet-valid claims fail validation\n401: 10. **TestLoadPublicKeyFromBase64**: Correctly loads base64-encoded PEM key\n402: 11. **TestLoadPublicKey_InvalidPEM**: Invalid PEM returns error\n403: 12. **TestAuthError_HTTPStatus**: Error types map to correct HTTP codes\n404: \n405: ### Integration Tests\n406: \n407: 1. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_FullFlow**: Full HTTP request with valid token\n408: 2. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_MultipleRequests**: Multiple concurrent requests\n409: 3. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_KeyRotation**: Server handles key change (restart)\n410: 4. **TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_HealthEndpoint**: Health endpoint with/without auth\n411: \n412: ### Test Fixtures\n413: \n414: ```go\n415: // generateTestToken creates a signed JWT token for testing\n416: func generateTestToken(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, claims *Claims) (string, error)\n417: \n418: // testClaims returns standard test claims\n419: func testClaims() *Claims {\n420:     return &Claims{\n421:         Sub:       \"test-user\",\n422:         Iss:       \"test-issuer\",\n423:         Aud:       \"picod\",\n424:         Exp:       time.Now().Add(1 * time.Hour).Unix(),\n425:         Iat:       time.Now().Unix(),\n426:         SandboxID: \"test-sandbox\",\n427:         Namespace: \"default\",\n428:     }\n429: }\n430: \n431: // generateTestKeyPair creates a test RSA key pair\n432: func generateTestKeyPair() (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ## Acceptance Criteria\n436: \n437: - [ ] JWT middleware correctly validates tokens\n438: - [ ] Invalid/missing tokens return 401 Unauthorized\n439: - [ ] Expired tokens are rejected\n440: - [ ] Signature verification works with RSA public key\n441: - [ ] Configurable skip paths work correctly\n442: - [ ] Health endpoint can be protected or public\n443: - [ ] Claims are correctly parsed and validated\n444: - [ ] Error types map to appropriate HTTP status codes\n445: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n446: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n447: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n448: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n449: - [ ] Compatible with standard JWT libraries (e.g., PyJWT, jose)\n450: \n451: ## References\n452: \n453: - AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n454: - AR-013: Session Storage\n455: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n456: - `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n457: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n458: - `deployment/spec.md`: Deployment Configuration\n459: - RFC 7519: JSON Web Token (JWT)\n460: - RFC 7515: JSON Web Signature (JWS)\n\n(End of file - total 460 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP daemon in the `pkg/picod` module. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure API Access** - Protect PicoD HTTP endpoints with RSA-based JWT authentication\n2. **Token Validation** - Validate JWT tokens signed with RSA private keys using the corresponding public key\n3. **Request Authorization** - Intercept and authenticate incoming HTTP requests before allowing access to command execution APIs\n4. **Flexible Configuration** - Support configuration via environment variables and command-line flags\n5. **Health Endpoint Protection** - Optionally protect the health check endpoint with JWT authentication\n\nThis implementation builds upon the PicoD execution infrastructure established in AR-015 and provides the security layer required for multi-tenant code interpreter deployments.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md","time":{"start":1775861539610,"end":1775861539634}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861539651,"sessionID":"ses_286678f41ffeN9616wg6MWphlY","part":{"id":"prt_d79989e05001ZoFqpYfFFgkeBu","messageID":"msg_d79988854001NpsYDE5mP0vTLy","sessionID":"ses_286678f41ffeN9616wg6MWphlY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c47e8be6dd7d440d9e3b5f4b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-2 (In Progress) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Structure\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n20:   - Define `PicoD` struct with fields:\n21:     - `sandboxID string`\n22:     - `workDir string`\n23:     - `limits *ResourceLimits`\n24:     - `securityOpts *SecurityOptions`\n25:     - `logger klog.Logger`\n26:   - Implement `New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD` constructor\n27: \n28: ### Phase 2: Resource Limits\n29: \n30: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n31:   - Define `ResourceLimits` struct\n32:   - Define `SecurityOptions` struct\n33:   - Implement option builder pattern:\n34:     - `WithTimeout(d time.Duration) Option`\n35:     - `WithMaxMemory(bytes int64) Option`\n36:     - `WithMaxCPU(cores float64) Option`\n37:     - `WithMaxOutputSize(bytes int64) Option`\n38:     - `WithMaxProcesses(count int) Option`\n39:     - `WithUID(uid int) Option`\n40:     - `WithGID(gid int) Option`\n41:     - `WithReadOnlyFS() Option`\n42:     - `WithNoNetwork() Option`\n43: \n44: ### Phase 3: Command Execution\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n47:   - Define `Command` struct\n48:   - Define `CommandResult` struct\n49:   - Define `Process` struct\n50:   - Implement `Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)`\n51:   - Implement `Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)`\n52:   - Implement `Process.Wait() (*CommandResult, error)`\n53:   - Implement `Process.Kill(signal os.Signal) error`\n54: \n55: ### Phase 4: Output Handling\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/picod/output.go`\n58:   - Implement output capture with size limits\n59:   - Implement streaming output support\n60:   - Implement output buffer management\n61: \n62: ### Phase 5: Security\n63: \n64: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/picod/security.go`\n65:   - Implement command validation\n66:   - Implement allowlist checking\n67:   - Implement path traversal prevention\n68:   - Implement capability dropping\n69: \n70: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n71: \n72: #### Unit Tests\n73: \n74: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n75:   - Test `New()` with various options\n76:   - Test option builder functions\n77: \n78: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Test `Run()` success case\n79: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Test `Run()` timeout\n80: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Test `Run()` cancellation\n81: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Test `Run()` output capture\n82: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Test `Run()` exit code handling\n83: \n84: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Test `Start()` and `Wait()` lifecycle\n85: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Test `Process.Kill()`\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Test output size limits\n88: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Test streaming output\n89: \n90: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Test security validations\n91: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Test allowlist enforcement\n92: - [ ] **TEST-042**: Test path traversal prevention\n93: \n94: #### Integration Tests\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `pkg/picod/picod_integration_test.go`\n97: - [ ] **TEST-051**: Integration test full lifecycle\n98: - [ ] **TEST-052**: Integration test concurrent execution\n99: - [ ] **TEST-053**: Integration test resource limits enforcement\n100: \n101: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n102: \n103: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add godoc comments to all exported types\n104: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all exported functions\n105: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add usage examples\n106: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Document security considerations\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## Acceptance Criteria\n111: \n112: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n113: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n114: - [ ] Output capture and streaming work correctly\n115: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n116: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n117: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n118: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n119: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n120: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## Dependencies\n125: \n126: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n127: |------------|--------|-------|\n128: | `context` | Standard | Command cancellation |\n129: | `os/exec` | Standard | Command execution |\n130: | `syscall` | Standard | Process management |\n131: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Logging |\n132: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | Type definitions |\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Implementation Order\n137: \n138: ```\n139: TASK-001\n140:     ↓\n141: TASK-010\n142:     ↓\n143: TASK-020\n144:     ↓\n145: TASK-030\n146:     ↓\n147: TASK-040\n148:     ↓\n149: TEST-001 → TEST-053\n150:     ↓\n151: DOC-001 → DOC-004\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## Related ARs\n157: \n158: | AR | Title | Relationship |\n159: |----|-------|--------------|\n160: | AR-012 | Session Storage Interface | Base infrastructure |\n161: | AR-013 | Redis Storage Implementation | Storage backend |\n162: | AR-014 | Valkey Storage Implementation | Storage backend |\n163: | AR-015 | PicoD 命令执行 API | This implementation |\n\n(End of file - total 163 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design Stage | ST-2 (In Progress) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Structure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Define `PicoD` struct with fields:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775861539617,"end":1775861539650}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861539655,"sessionID":"ses_286678f41ffeN9616wg6MWphlY","part":{"id":"prt_d799898f4001VKYGsTJG7BTn1j","messageID":"msg_d79988854001NpsYDE5mP0vTLy","sessionID":"ses_286678f41ffeN9616wg6MWphlY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_70a230bf20a64319b5f5b75a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `FileType` type and constants in `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go`\n18:   - Types: `FileTypeRegular`, `FileTypeDirectory`, `FileTypeSymlink`, `FileTypeOther`\n19:   - String representation for each type\n20: \n21: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `FileInfo` struct in `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go`\n22:   - Fields: `Name` (string), `Path` (string), `Size` (int64), `Mode` (os.FileMode), `ModTime` (time.Time), `IsDir` (bool), `FileType` (FileType)\n23:   - Constructor: `NewFileInfo(path string, info os.FileInfo) (*FileInfo, error)`\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `FileQuota` struct in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n26:   - Fields: `MaxFileSize` (int64), `MaxTotalSize` (int64), `MaxFiles` (int64), `MaxDirectoryDepth` (int)\n27:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n28:   - Validation rules: MaxFileSize > 0, MaxTotalSize > 0, MaxFiles > 0, MaxDirectoryDepth > 0\n29: \n30: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `DefaultFileQuota()` function in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n31:   - Returns: MaxFileSize=10MB, MaxTotalSize=100MB, MaxFiles=1000, MaxDirectoryDepth=10\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define `QuotaUsage` struct in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n34:   - Fields: `UsedBytes` (int64), `MaxBytes` (int64), `FileCount` (int64), `MaxFiles` (int64), `PercentUsed` (float64)\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-006**: Define `FileErrorType` and error constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n37:   - Types: `FileErrorNotFound`, `FileErrorPermission`, `FileErrorQuotaExceeded`, `FileErrorPathTraversal`, `FileErrorWrite`, `FileErrorRead`, `FileErrorSymlink`, `FileErrorDepth`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `FileError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n40:   - Fields: `Type` (FileErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n41:   - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n42: \n43: ### Phase 2: Path Validation Utilities\n44: \n45: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ValidatePath()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n46:   - Validates path is within workspace boundary\n47:   - Returns absolute path or error\n48:   - Prevents path traversal attacks\n49: \n50: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `ResolvePath()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n51:   - Resolves path to absolute, following symlinks\n52:   - Returns error if symlink target is outside workspace\n53: \n54: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `GetDepth()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n55:   - Calculates directory depth of a path\n56:   - Returns depth as integer\n57: \n58: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `IsWithinWorkspace()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n59:   - Checks if resolved path is within workspace\n60:   - Uses filepath.Abs and strings.HasPrefix\n61: \n62: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `ValidateDepth()` function in `pkg/picod/path.go`\n63:   - Validates path depth does not exceed maximum\n64:   - Returns error if depth exceeds limit\n65: \n66: ### Phase 3: FileSystem Interface Definition\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `FileSystem` interface in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n69:   - Methods:\n70:     - `Read(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)`\n71:     - `ReadStream(ctx context.Context, path string) (io.ReadCloser, error)`\n72:     - `Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error`\n73:     - `WriteStream(ctx context.Context, path string, reader io.Reader, size int64) error`\n74:     - `Delete(ctx context.Context, path string) error`\n75:     - `DeleteAll(ctx context.Context, path string) error`\n76:     - `Exists(ctx context.Context, path string) (bool, error)`\n77:     - `Info(ctx context.Context, path string) (*FileInfo, error)`\n78:     - `List(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)`\n79:     - `Mkdir(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error`\n80:     - `MkdirAll(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error`\n81:     - `Rename(ctx context.Context, oldPath, newPath string) error`\n82:     - `Copy(ctx context.Context, srcPath, dstPath string) error`\n83:     - `Quota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)`\n84: \n85: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `fileSystem` struct in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n86:   - Fields: `workDir` (string), `quota` (*FileQuota), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n87:   - Implements FileSystem interface\n88: \n89: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `NewFileSystem()` constructor in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n90:   - Creates fileSystem instance with workDir, quota, logger\n91: \n92: ### Phase 4: File Read Operations\n93: \n94: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `Read()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n95:   - Flow: ValidatePath → Check exists → Read file → Return []byte\n96:   - Handle FileErrorNotFound, FileErrorPathTraversal, FileErrorRead\n97: \n98: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `ReadStream()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n99:   - Opens file with streaming support\n100:   - Returns io.ReadCloser\n101:   - Validates path before opening\n102: \n103: ### Phase 5: File Write Operations\n104: \n105: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `Write()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n106:   - Flow: ValidatePath → Check quota → Write temp file → Atomic rename\n107:   - Uses temporary file + os.Rename for atomicity\n108:   - Handle FileErrorQuotaExceeded, FileErrorWrite\n109: \n110: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `WriteStream()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n111:   - Writes from io.Reader with size limit\n112:   - Enforces MaxFileSize quota during write\n113:   - Atomic write using temp file\n114: \n115: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `calculateQuotaUsage()` helper in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n116:   - Walks directory tree to calculate total size and file count\n117:   - Returns current quota usage statistics\n118: \n119: ### Phase 6: File Delete Operations\n120: \n121: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `Delete()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n122:   - Removes single file or empty directory\n123:   - Validates path before deletion\n124:   - Handle FileErrorNotFound, FileErrorPermission\n125: \n126: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `DeleteAll()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n127:   - Removes directory and all contents recursively\n128:   - Uses os.RemoveAll with path validation\n129:   - Logs deletion for audit trail\n130: \n131: ### Phase 7: File Metadata Operations\n132: \n133: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `Exists()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n134:   - Checks if path exists\n135:   - Returns (bool, error)\n136:   - Handles path validation\n137: \n138: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `Info()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n139:   - Returns file metadata as *FileInfo\n140:   - Uses os.Stat and NewFileInfo\n141:   - Handle FileErrorNotFound\n142: \n143: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `List()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n144:   - Lists directory contents\n145:   - Returns []FileInfo\n146:   - Reads directory with os.ReadDir\n147:   - Filters and validates each entry\n148: \n149: ### Phase 8: Directory Operations\n150: \n151: - [ ] **TASK-070**: Implement `Mkdir()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n152:   - Creates single directory\n153:   - Validates depth limit\n154:   - Handle FileErrorDepth, FileErrorWrite\n155: \n156: - [ ] **TASK-071**: Implement `MkdirAll()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n157:   - Creates directory and all parent directories\n158:   - Validates depth limit for full path\n159:   - Handle FileErrorDepth\n160: \n161: ### Phase 9: File Move/Copy Operations\n162: \n163: - [ ] **TASK-080**: Implement `Rename()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n164:   - Renames/moves file or directory\n165:   - Validates both oldPath and newPath\n166:   - Ensures target is within workspace\n167:   - Handle FileErrorPathTraversal\n168: \n169: - [ ] **TASK-081**: Implement `Copy()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n170:   - Copies file from srcPath to dstPath\n171:   - Validates both paths\n172:   - Checks quota before copy\n173:   - Preserves file permissions\n174: \n175: ### Phase 10: Quota Management\n176: \n177: - [ ] **TASK-090**: Implement `Quota()` method in `pkg/picod/filesystem.go`\n178:   - Returns current quota usage\n179:   - Calls calculateQuotaUsage\n180:   - Calculates PercentUsed\n181: \n182: - [ ] **TASK-091**: Implement `checkWriteQuota()` helper in `pkg/picod/quota.go`\n183:   - Validates write operation against quota\n184:   - Checks file size limit\n185:   - Checks total size limit\n186:   - Checks file count limit\n187:   - Returns FileErrorQuotaExceeded if exceeded\n188: \n189: ### Phase 11: PicoD Integration\n190: \n191: - [ ] **TASK-100**: Add `fileQuota` field to `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n192:   - Field: `fileQuota *FileQuota`\n193: \n194: - [ ] **TASK-101**: Add `fs` field to `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n195:   - Field: `fs FileSystem`\n196: \n197: - [ ] **TASK-102**: Add `WithFileQuota()` option in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n198:   - Functional option to set file quota\n199: \n200: - [ ] **TASK-103**: Implement `FileSystem()` method in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n201:   - Returns FileSystem interface\n202: \n203: - [ ] **TASK-104**: Implement convenience methods in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n204:   - `ReadFile(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)`\n205:   - `WriteFile(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error`\n206:   - `ListDir(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)`\n207:   - `DeleteFile(ctx context.Context, path string) error`\n208:   - `GetQuota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)`\n209: \n210: - [ ] **TASK-105**: Initialize FileSystem in `New()` constructor\n211:   - Create FileSystem with workDir, fileQuota, logger\n212:   - Assign to p.fs field\n213: \n214: ### Phase 12: Configuration\n215: \n216: - [ ] **TASK-110**: Update `Config` struct in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n217:   - Add fields: `QuotaMaxFileSize`, `QuotaMaxTotalSize`, `QuotaMaxFiles`, `QuotaMaxDepth`\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TASK-111**: Update `LoadConfig()` in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n220:   - Load from environment variables:\n221:     - `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_FILE_SIZE` (default: 10MB)\n222:     - `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_TOTAL_SIZE` (default: 100MB)\n223:     - `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_FILES` (default: 1000)\n224:     - `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_DEPTH` (default: 10)\n225: \n226: ### Phase 13: Unit Tests\n227: \n228: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestFileInfo_NewFileInfo` in `pkg/picod/fileinfo_test.go`\n229:   - Test regular file info extraction\n230:   - Test directory info extraction\n231:   - Test symlink info extraction\n232:   - Verify all fields populated correctly\n233: \n234: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestFileQuota_Validate` in `pkg/picod/quota_test.go`\n235:   - Valid quota → no error\n236:   - MaxFileSize<=0 → error\n237:   - MaxTotalSize<=0 → error\n238:   - MaxFiles<=0 → error\n239:   - MaxDirectoryDepth<=0 → error\n240: \n241: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestValidatePath_Success` in `pkg/picod/path_test.go`\n242:   - Valid relative path → absolute path returned\n243:   - Valid absolute path within workspace → same path returned\n244:   - Normalized path (removes ..) → correct absolute path\n245: \n246: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestValidatePath_PathTraversal` in `pkg/picod/path_test.go`\n247:   - Path with ../ escaping workspace → FileErrorPathTraversal\n248:   - Absolute path outside workspace → FileErrorPathTraversal\n249:   - Symlink to outside workspace → FileErrorPathTraversal\n250: \n251: - [ ] **TEST-005**: Create `TestGetDepth` in `pkg/picod/path_test.go`\n252:   - Root path → depth 0\n253:   - One level deep → depth 1\n254:   - Multiple levels → correct depth count\n255: \n256: - [ ] **TEST-006**: Create `TestFileSystem_Read_Success` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n257:   - Read existing file → returns correct []byte\n258:   - Verify no error\n259: \n260: - [ ] **TEST-007**: Create `TestFileSystem_Read_NotFound` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n261:   - Read non-existent file → FileErrorNotFound\n262: \n263: - [ ] **TEST-008**: Create `TestFileSystem_Read_PathTraversal` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n264:   - Read with path traversal → FileErrorPathTraversal\n265: \n266: - [ ] **TEST-009**: Create `TestFileSystem_Write_Success` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n267:   - Write new file → file created\n268:   - Verify file contents match\n269:   - Verify atomic write (no .tmp file left)\n270: \n271: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestFileSystem_Write_Atomic` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n272:   - Write interrupted → no partial file\n273:   - Verify atomic rename behavior\n274: \n275: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestFileSystem_Write_QuotaExceeded` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n276:   - Write exceeds MaxFileSize → FileErrorQuotaExceeded\n277:   - Write exceeds MaxTotalSize → FileErrorQuotaExceeded\n278: \n279: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Create `TestFileSystem_Delete_Success` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n280:   - Delete existing file → file removed\n281:   - Delete empty directory → directory removed\n282: \n283: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Create `TestFileSystem_Delete_All` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n284:   - Delete directory with contents → all contents removed\n285:   - Verify recursive deletion\n286: \n287: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Create `TestFileSystem_Exists` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n288:   - Existing file → true\n289:   - Non-existent file → false\n290: \n291: - [ ] **TEST-015**: Create `TestFileSystem_Info` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n292:   - Get info on file → correct FileInfo\n293:   - Verify Size, Mode, ModTime, FileType\n294: \n295: - [ ] **TEST-016**: Create `TestFileSystem_List` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n296:   - List directory → correct []FileInfo\n297:   - Verify all entries included\n298: \n299: - [ ] **TEST-017**: Create `TestFileSystem_Mkdir` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n300:   - Create directory → directory exists\n301:   - Create with depth limit → FileErrorDepth\n302: \n303: - [ ] **TEST-018**: Create `TestFileSystem_Rename` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n304:   - Rename file → file moved\n305:   - Rename outside workspace → FileErrorPathTraversal\n306: \n307: - [ ] **TEST-019**: Create `TestFileSystem_Copy` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n308:   - Copy file → new file with same contents\n309:   - Verify permissions preserved\n310: \n311: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `TestFileSystem_Quota` in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n312:   - Get quota usage → correct UsedBytes, FileCount\n313:   - Verify PercentUsed calculated correctly\n314: \n315: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `TestFileError_ErrorTypes` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n316:   - Verify all error types implemented\n317:   - Verify Error() and Unwrap() work correctly\n318: \n319: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create `TestPicoD_ReadFile` in `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n320:   - Convenience method reads file correctly\n321: \n322: - [ ] **TEST-023**: Create `TestPicoD_WriteFile` in `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n323:   - Convenience method writes file correctly\n324: \n325: - [ ] **TEST-024**: Create `TestPicoD_GetQuota` in `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n326:   - Convenience method returns quota usage\n327: \n328: - [ ] **TEST-025**: Create `TestLoadConfig_FileQuota` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n329:   - Load file quota from environment\n330:   - Verify defaults applied\n331: \n332: ### Phase 14: Integration Tests\n333: \n334: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `TestFileSystem_Integration_FullLifecycle` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n335:   - Create → Write → Read → List → Rename → Copy → Delete lifecycle\n336:   - Verify end-to-end functionality\n337: \n338: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Create `TestFileSystem_Integration_Concurrent` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n339:   - Concurrent file operations\n340:   - Verify isolation and no race conditions\n341:   - Run with -race flag\n342: \n343: - [ ] **TEST-032**: Create `TestFileSystem_Integration_QuotaEnforcement` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n344:   - Fill up quota gradually\n345:   - Verify enforcement at limit\n346:   - Verify accurate usage tracking\n347: \n348: - [ ] **TEST-033**: Create `TestFileSystem_Integration_AtomicWrite` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n349:   - Atomic write under concurrent load\n350:   - Verify no partial writes visible\n351: \n352: - [ ] **TEST-034**: Create `TestFileSystem_Integration_LargeFiles` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n353:   - Write files near size limit\n354:   - Verify handling of large files\n355:   - Verify quota enforcement\n356: \n357: - [ ] **TEST-035**: Create `TestFileSystem_Integration_DeepDirectories` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n358:   - Create directories at depth limit\n359:   - Verify depth enforcement\n360:   - Verify GetDepth accuracy\n361: \n362: ### Phase 15: Documentation\n363: \n364: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types and functions\n365:   - Include parameter descriptions\n366:   - Include return value descriptions\n367:   - Include error conditions\n368: \n369: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Create usage examples in doc comments\n370:   - Example: creating FileSystem\n371:   - Example: reading file\n372:   - Example: writing file atomically\n373:   - Example: quota management\n374: \n375: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update `pkg/picod/README.md`\n376:   - Document file management API\n377:   - Include configuration options\n378:   - Include error handling guide\n379:   - Include security considerations\n380: \n381: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add security documentation\n382:   - Path traversal prevention\n383:   - Symlink attack prevention\n384:   - Quota enforcement\n385:   - Audit logging\n386: \n387: ## Acceptance Criteria\n388: \n389: - [ ] FileSystem interface implements all required methods\n390: - [ ] Path validation prevents operations outside workspace\n391: - [ ] Quota enforcement works correctly (size, file count, depth)\n392: - [ ] Atomic writes prevent partial file corruption\n393: - [ ] Symlink attacks are prevented\n394: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n395: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n396: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n397: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n398: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n399: - [ ] File operations are logged for audit trail\n400: - [ ] Each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n401: \n402: ## Dependencies\n403: \n404: | Dependency | Status |\n405: |------------|--------|\n406: | Go 1.21+ | Required |\n407: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | Required |\n408: | context package | Required |\n409: | io/fs package | Required |\n410: | path/filepath package | Required |\n411: | syscall package | Required |\n412: | AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API) | Completed |\n413: | AR-012 (Sandbox Infrastructure) | Completed |\n414: \n415: ## Implementation Order\n416: \n417: ```\n418: TASK-001 → TASK-007 (Data structures)\n419:     ↓\n420: TASK-010 → TASK-014 (Path utilities)\n421:     ↓\n422: TASK-020 → TASK-022 (FileSystem interface)\n423:     ↓\n424: TASK-030 → TASK-091 (File operations implementation)\n425:     ↓\n426: TASK-100 → TASK-105 (PicoD integration)\n427:     ↓\n428: TASK-110 → TASK-111 (Configuration)\n429:     ↓\n430: TEST-001 → TEST-025 (Unit tests)\n431:     ↓\n432: TEST-030 → TEST-035 (Integration tests)\n433:     ↓\n434: DOC-001 → DOC-004 (Documentation)\n435: ```\n436: \n437: ## Test Infrastructure\n438: \n439: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `mockFileSystem` helper in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n440:   - Creates test FileSystem with temp directory\n441:   - Returns cleanup function\n442: \n443: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Create `createTestFile` helper in `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go`\n444:   - Creates test file with specific size\n445:   - Used for quota testing\n446: \n447: - [ ] **TEST-042**: Create test fixtures for common scenarios\n448:   - Pre-populated directory structure\n449:   - Files with various permissions\n450:   - Symlinks for testing\n451: \n452: ## Coverage Verification\n453: \n454: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n455:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/picod/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n456:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n457:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n458:   - Verify filesystem.go, quota.go, path.go, fileinfo.go all covered\n\n(End of file - total 458 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `FileType` type and constants in `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go`\n  - Types: `FileTypeRegular`, `FileTypeDirectory`, `FileTypeSymlink`, `FileTypeOther`\n  - String representation for each type\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775861539614,"end":1775861539652}}}}
