{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861632587,"sessionID":"ses_286678f41ffeN9616wg6MWphlY","part":{"id":"prt_d7998af2e001KiAgRubFb3ITdi","messageID":"msg_d7998a379001uvBlECiDkSEMTM","sessionID":"ses_286678f41ffeN9616wg6MWphlY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_7f9648262bec4532bfc50bd3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","content":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n  - Define package-level imports: `crypto/rsa`, `crypto/x509`, `encoding/pem`, `encoding/base64`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `LoadPublicKey(pemData []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n  - Parse PEM block from data\n  - Delegate to ParsePEM for key extraction\n  - Return error if PEM parsing fails\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Implement `LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(base64PEM string) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n  - Decode base64 string to bytes\n  - Call LoadPublicKey with decoded bytes\n  - Handle base64 decoding errors\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `ParsePEM(pemBlock *pem.Block) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n  - Handle PKIX format (x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey)\n  - Handle PKCS#1 format (x509.ParsePKCS1PublicKey)\n  - Return error for unsupported formats\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `GenerateKeyPair(bits int) (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n  - Generate RSA key pair using rsa.GenerateKey\n  - Return private and public keys\n  - Use crypto/rand for secure random generation\n\n### Phase 2: JWT Claims & Validation (`jwt.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `Claims` struct in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n  - Fields: `Sub` (string), `Iss` (string), `Aud` (string), `Exp` (int64), `Iat` (int64), `SandboxID` (string), `Namespace` (string)\n  - JSON tags for all fields\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Validate(c *Claims, now time.Time, clockSkew time.Duration) error` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n  - Check expiration (exp + clockSkew < now → expired)\n  - Check not before (iat - clockSkew > now → not yet valid)\n  - Validate required claims (sub, iss, aud, exp, iat present)\n  - Return appropriate error for each validation failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `ParseAndValidate(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, clockSkew time.Duration) (*Claims, error)` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n  - Split token into header.payload.signature\n  - Verify signature using VerifySignature\n  - Parse payload JSON into Claims\n  - Validate claims using Validate\n  - Return parsed claims or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `VerifySignature(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) error` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n  - Decode header and payload (base64url)\n  - Decode signature (base64url)\n  - Construct signing input: `header.payload`\n  - Verify RSA-PKCS1v15 signature (SHA256)\n  - Return error if signature invalid\n\n### Phase 3: Authentication Errors (`errors.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `AuthErrorType` type and constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n  - Type: `AuthErrorType` (string alias)\n  - Constants: `AuthErrorMissingToken`, `AuthErrorInvalidToken`, `AuthErrorExpiredToken`, `AuthErrorInvalidSig`, `AuthErrorInvalidClaims`, `AuthErrorInternal`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `AuthError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n  - Fields: `Type` (AuthErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n  - Methods: `Error() string`, `Unwrap() error`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `HTTPStatus(e *AuthError) int` in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n  - Map error types to HTTP status codes:\n    - MissingToken, InvalidToken, InvalidSig, InvalidClaims → 401\n    - ExpiredToken → 401\n    - Internal → 500\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `NewAuthError(authType AuthErrorType, message string, underlying error) *AuthError` in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n  - Constructor for AuthError\n  - Format message with context\n\n### Phase 4: HTTP Middleware (`middleware.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Define `JWTMiddleware` struct in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n  - Fields: `publicKey` (*rsa.PublicKey), `skipPaths` (map[string]bool), `clockSkew` (time.Duration), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, clockSkew time.Duration, skipPaths ...string) *JWTMiddleware` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n  - Initialize skipPaths map\n  - Set default clockSkew (30 seconds if 0)\n  - Create structured logger\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Middleware(m *JWTMiddleware, next http.Handler) http.Handler` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n  - Wrap handler with authentication logic\n  - Extract path from request\n  - Check if path should skip auth\n  - Extract token from Authorization header\n  - Validate token\n  - Call next handler on success, return error on failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `extractToken(m *JWTMiddleware, r *http.Request) (string, error)` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n  - Get Authorization header\n  - Validate \"Bearer \" prefix\n  - Extract token string\n  - Return error if missing or malformed\n\n- [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `shouldSkip(m *JWTMiddleware, path string) bool` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n  - Check if path exists in skipPaths map\n  - Support exact path matching\n\n### Phase 5: HTTP Response Helpers (`middleware.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `WriteJSON(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n  - Set Content-Type header\n  - Set status code\n  - Encode data as JSON\n  - Handle encoding errors\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `WriteAuthError(w http.ResponseWriter, err *AuthError)` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n  - Get HTTP status from error\n  - Write JSON error response\n  - Include error type and message\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Define `HealthResponse` struct in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n  - Fields: `Status` (string), `Timestamp` (time.Time), `SandboxID` (string)\n  - JSON tags for all fields\n\n### Phase 6: Configuration (`config.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Add auth fields to `Config` struct in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n  - Fields: `AuthMode` (string), `PublicKeyPEM` (string), `SkipPaths` ([]string), `ClockSkew` (time.Duration)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Update `LoadConfig()` in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n  - Load `PICOD_AUTH_MODE` (default: \"none\")\n  - Load `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` (required if AuthMode=picod)\n  - Load `PICOD_AUTH_SKIP_PATHS` (default: \"/health\", comma-separated)\n  - Load `PICOD_AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW` (default: 30s)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-052**: Add command-line flag parsing helpers in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n  - `ParseAuthFlags()` function\n  - Flags: `-auth`, `-public-key`, `-skip-paths`, `-clock-skew`\n  - Merge flags with environment variables (flags take precedence)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `Validate(c *Config) error` for auth config in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n  - If AuthMode=\"picod\", require PublicKeyPEM\n  - Validate clockSkew is non-negative\n  - Parse and validate skip paths\n\n### Phase 7: PicoD Integration (`picod.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Add `authMode` and `publicKey` fields to `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Fields: `authMode` (string), `publicKey` (*rsa.PublicKey)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-061**: Add `WithAuthMode(mode string) Option` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Functional option to set auth mode\n\n- [ ] **TASK-062**: Add `WithPublicKey(pem string) Option` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Functional option to set public key\n  - Load key from PEM\n\n- [ ] **TASK-063**: Implement `SetupHTTPServer(picod *PicoD, config *Config) (*http.Server, error)` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Create ServeMux\n  - Register handlers\n  - Apply JWT middleware if AuthMode=picod\n  - Configure ReadHeaderTimeout (10s)\n\n### Phase 8: Unit Tests\n\n#### Crypto Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestLoadPublicKey_Success` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n  - Load valid PKIX PEM key\n  - Verify key returned without error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestLoadPublicKeyFromBase64` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n  - Load base64-encoded PEM key\n  - Verify decoded key matches direct load\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestLoadPublicKey_InvalidPEM` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n  - Load invalid PEM data\n  - Verify error returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestGenerateKeyPair` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n  - Generate key pair (2048 bits)\n  - Verify private and public keys not nil\n\n#### JWT Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Success` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Valid claims with future exp\n  - Verify no error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Expired` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Claims with past exp\n  - Verify error returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Future` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Claims with future iat\n  - Verify error returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_MissingClaims` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Claims missing required fields\n  - Verify error returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: Create `TestParseAndValidate_Success` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Generate valid token with test key\n  - Parse and validate\n  - Verify claims extracted correctly\n\n- [ ] **TEST-015**: Create `TestParseAndValidate_InvalidSignature` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Tamper with token signature\n  - Verify signature verification fails\n\n- [ ] **TEST-016**: Create `TestVerifySignature_RS256` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Verify RS256 signature algorithm\n  - Test with known token\n\n#### Error Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `TestAuthError_ErrorTypes` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n  - Verify all error types defined\n  - Verify Error() method works\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `TestAuthError_HTTPStatus` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n  - Each error type maps to correct HTTP status\n  - 401 for auth errors, 500 for internal\n\n#### Middleware Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_ValidToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n  - Request with valid JWT token\n  - Verify next handler called\n  - Verify request passes through\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_MissingToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n  - Request without Authorization header\n  - Verify 401 returned\n  - Verify next handler not called\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n  - Request with malformed token\n  - Verify 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-033**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_ExpiredToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n  - Request with expired token\n  - Verify 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-034**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_SkipPath` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n  - Request to /health (skipped path)\n  - Verify auth not required\n  - Verify next handler called\n\n- [ ] **TEST-035**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidAuthHeader` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n  - Request with non-Bearer auth scheme\n  - Verify 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-036**: Create `TestExtractToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n  - Valid Bearer header → token extracted\n  - Missing header → error\n  - Malformed header → error\n\n#### Config Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `TestLoadConfig_AuthConfig` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n  - Load auth config from environment\n  - Verify defaults applied\n\n- [ ] **TEST-041**: Create `TestConfig_Validate_AuthMode` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n  - AuthMode=picod without key → error\n  - AuthMode=picod with key → valid\n  - AuthMode=none → valid\n\n### Phase 9: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_FullFlow` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Start real HTTP server with JWT middleware\n  - Make request with valid token\n  - Verify 200 OK\n  - Make request without token\n  - Verify 401 Unauthorized\n\n- [ ] **TEST-051**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_MultipleRequests` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Concurrent requests with valid tokens\n  - Verify all succeed\n  - Verify no race conditions (run with -race)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-052**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_HealthEndpoint` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Health endpoint without token → 200 OK\n  - Protected endpoint without token → 401\n  - Verify skip paths work in real server\n\n- [ ] **TEST-053**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_TokenTampering` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Modify valid token payload\n  - Verify signature check fails\n  - Verify 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-054**: Create `TestSetupHTTPServer_Integration` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Full server setup with auth enabled\n  - Verify middleware applied\n  - Verify server responds correctly\n\n### Phase 10: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types in `crypto.go`, `jwt.go`, `errors.go`, `middleware.go`\n  - Include parameter descriptions\n  - Include return value descriptions\n  - Include error conditions\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add usage examples in doc comments\n  - Example: creating JWT middleware\n  - Example: loading public key\n  - Example: validating token\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Update `pkg/picod/README.md`\n  - Document JWT authentication\n  - Include configuration options\n  - Include token format requirements\n  - Include error handling guide\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Add security documentation\n  - RSA key management best practices\n  - Token lifetime recommendations\n  - Clock skew considerations\n  - Key rotation strategy\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] JWT middleware correctly validates tokens with RSA signatures\n- [ ] Invalid/missing tokens return 401 Unauthorized\n- [ ] Expired tokens are rejected\n- [ ] Signature verification works with RSA public key (PKIX and PKCS#1 formats)\n- [ ] Configurable skip paths work correctly\n- [ ] Health endpoint can be protected or public\n- [ ] Claims are correctly parsed and validated (exp, iat, sub, iss, aud)\n- [ ] Clock skew tolerance is configurable\n- [ ] Error types map to appropriate HTTP status codes\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n- [ ] Compatible with standard JWT libraries (PyJWT, node-jose, etc.)\n- [ ] RS256 (RSA-PKCS1v15 with SHA256) signature algorithm implemented\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA signature verification |\n| `crypto/x509` | Standard | X.509 key parsing |\n| `crypto/rand` | Standard | Key generation |\n| `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM decoding |\n| `encoding/base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding |\n| `encoding/json` | Standard | JSON claims parsing |\n| `net/http` | Standard | HTTP middleware |\n| `strings` | Standard | String manipulation |\n| `time` | Standard | Token time validation |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n| AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n| AR-016 (PicoD File Management API) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001 → TASK-005 (Crypto utilities)\n    ↓\nTASK-010 → TASK-013 (JWT claims & validation)\n    ↓\nTASK-020 → TASK-023 (Auth errors)\n    ↓\nTASK-030 → TASK-034 (HTTP middleware)\n    ↓\nTASK-040 → TASK-042 (Response helpers)\n    ↓\nTASK-050 → TASK-053 (Configuration)\n    ↓\nTASK-060 → TASK-063 (PicoD integration)\n    ↓\nTEST-001 → TEST-041 (Unit tests)\n    ↓\nTEST-050 → TEST-054 (Integration tests)\n    ↓\nDOC-001 → DOC-004 (Documentation)\n```\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **TEST-060**: Create `generateTestToken(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, claims *Claims) (string, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Create JWT header (RS256)\n  - Encode claims as JSON\n  - Sign with private key\n  - Return complete token\n\n- [ ] **TEST-061**: Create `testClaims() *Claims` helper in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n  - Return standard test claims with valid timestamps\n\n- [ ] **TEST-062**: Create `generateTestKeyPair() (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n  - Generate RSA key pair for tests\n  - Use smaller key size (1024 bits) for speed\n\n- [ ] **TEST-063**: Create `newTestServer(handler http.Handler) (*httptest.Server, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Create test HTTP server\n  - Return server and cleanup function\n\n## Coverage Verification\n\n- [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n  - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/picod/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n  - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n  - Verify crypto.go, jwt.go, errors.go, middleware.go all covered\n  - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- [ ] **SEC-001**: Verify RSA signature uses SHA256 (RS256)\n- [ ] **SEC-002**: Verify clock skew prevents replay attacks\n- [ ] **SEC-003**: Verify token parsing rejects malformed input\n- [ ] **SEC-004**: Verify key loading rejects invalid formats\n- [ ] **SEC-005**: Verify error messages don't leak sensitive info\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775861632572,"end":1775861632583}}}}
